<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — <code>load_level</code> should turn the data into real game objects. Right now the enemies don't move because they were never made into <code>Enemy</code> objects.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">def load_level(idx):
    data = LEVELS[idx]
    platforms = [pygame.Rect(*p) for p in data[&quot;platforms&quot;]]
    coins = [pygame.Rect(c[0], c[1], 20, 20) for c in data[&quot;coins&quot;]]
    enemies = data[&quot;enemies&quot;]
    finish = pygame.Rect(*data[&quot;finish&quot;])
    return platforms, coins, enemies, finish
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> the enemy tuples need to become <code>Enemy(...)</code> objects, like the platforms became <code>Rect</code>s.</p>
